                    <floruit source="#bib1093-1" notBefore="0335" syriaca-computed-start="0335" notAfter="0385" syriaca-computed-end="0385">0335-0385</floruit>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1093-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1093-1">Peeters, Martyrologe, 163. Barsaum, Lu'lu 625, BS I, 13 (B. Cignitti) - acts of these martyrs in MS in the Library of the Syrian Orthodox patriarchate, Berlin (Sachau 241) and garshuni in the British Museum- unpublished
Barsaum, Lu 'lu ' 2 , 625.
BS, I, 13 (B. Cignitti).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">In hagiography: Abai was a Persian
          Martyr killed by his father, <persName>Adorpirozgerd</persName>, who later converted to
          Christianity. He was mentioned in the legend of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1436">Saba Pirgushnasp</persName>. He was martyred with
          his mother <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1274">Astina (Hwarta)</persName> and
          5000 friends.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1093-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on 1 or 2 October.</desc>
                    </event>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1093-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Bibliotheca Hagiographica Syriaca</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/649"/>
